{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d45-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3154"},"text":"§ 3154.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Contingency contracting matters covered","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d46-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The joint policy for contingency contracting required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3151"},"text":"section 3151 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall, at a minimum, provide for the following:"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d47-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The designation of a senior commissioned officer or civilian member of the senior executive service in each military department with the responsibility for administering the policy.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d48-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The assignment of a senior commissioned officer with appropriate acquisition experience and qualifications to act as head of contingency contracting during combat operations, post-conflict operations, and contingency operations, who shall report directly to the commander of the combatant command in whose area of responsibility the operations occur.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d49-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A sourcing approach to contingency contracting that is designed to ensure that each military department is prepared to conduct contingency contracting during combat operations, post-conflict operations, and contingency operations, including stabilization and reconstruction operations involving interagency organizations, if required.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d4a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A requirement to provide training (including training under a program to be created by the Defense Acquisition University) to contingency contracting personnel in—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d4b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the use of law, regulations, policies, and directives related to contingency contracting operations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d4c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the appropriate use of rapid acquisition methods, including the use of exceptions to competition requirements under sections 3201 through 3205 of this title, sealed bidding, letter contracts, indefinite delivery-indefinite quantity task orders, set asides under section 8(a) of the Small Business Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s637/a"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 637(a)","children":[],"tail":"), undefinitized contract actions, and other tools available to expedite the delivery of goods and services during combat operations or post-conflict operations;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d4d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/4/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the appropriate use of rapid acquisition authority, commanders’ emergency response program funds, and other tools unique to contingency contracting; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d4e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/4/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" instruction on the necessity for the prompt transition from the use of rapid acquisition authority to the use of full and open competition and other methods of contracting that maximize transparency in the acquisition process.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d4f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Appropriate steps to ensure that training is maintained for such personnel even when they are not deployed in a contingency operation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d50-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Such steps as may be needed to ensure jointness and cross-service coordination in the area of contingency contracting.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d51-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3154/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Interagency Plans","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"To the extent practicable, the joint policy for contingency contracting required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3151"},"text":"section 3151 of this title","children":[],"tail":" should be taken into account in the development of interagency plans for stabilization and reconstruction operations, consistent with the report submitted by the President under section 1035 of the John Warner National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2007 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/364"},"text":"Public Law 109–364","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2388"},"text":"120 Stat. 2388","children":[],"tail":") on interagency operating procedures for the planning and conduct of stabilization and reconstruction operations."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa0c9d52-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1810/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1810(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b)(4), (c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4162-4164"},"text":"134 Stat. 4162–4164","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa0c9d53-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa0c9d54-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idaa0c9d55-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 1035 of the John Warner National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2007, referred to in subsec. (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/364/s1035"},"text":"section 1035 of Pub. L. 109–364","children":[],"tail":", div. A, title X, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2388"},"text":"120 Stat. 2388","children":[],"tail":", which is not classified to the Code."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa0c9d56-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The text of subsec. (d) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2333"},"text":"section 2333 of this title","children":[],"tail":", which was transferred to this section and amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1810/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1810(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", (c), was based on "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/364/dA/tVIII/s854/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–364, div. A, title VIII, § 854(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2343"},"text":"120 Stat. 2343","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/84/dA/tX/s1073/a/23/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–84, div. A, title X, § 1073(a)(23)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/2473"},"text":"123 Stat. 2473","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaa0c9d57-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1810/b/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1810(b)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (C), (D), substituted “In General” for “Contingency Contracting Matters Covered” in heading and “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3151"},"text":"section 3151 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” for “subsection (a)” in introductory provisions, struck out par. (1) designation at beginning, redesignated subpars. (A) to (F) as pars. (1) to (6), respectively, and, in par. (4), redesignated cls. (i) to (iv) as subpars. (A) to (D), respectively. Former par. (2) redesignated subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1810/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1810(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (d) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2333"},"text":"section 2333 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as subsec. (a) of this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1810/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1810(c)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “sections 3201 through 3205” for “section 2304”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1810/b/4/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1810(b)(4)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (C), redesignated par. (2) of subsec. (a) as subsec. (b), inserted heading, and substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3151"},"text":"section 3151 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” for “subsection (a)”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idaa0c9d58-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idaa0c9d59-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section and amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2022","children":[],"tail":", with additional provisions for delayed implementation and applicability of existing law, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1801/d"},"text":"section 1801(d) of Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 2021 Amendment note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
